<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><input type="hidden" name="PHPSESSID" value="...328fedb22570524062aeb1303" /><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/vs/articles/index.php3'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/heroclix/articles/articles.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/articles/articles.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/articles/articles.php'>Ophidian 2350</option><option value='/magic/treports/treports.php'>The Wastelands</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Stupid Change of Plans Tricks<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(4.43)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=4282'>Joshua "Stormcrow" Grace</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=4282&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> September 1, 2003</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont"> I don&#39;t have the opportunity to play in many tournaments these days since there are none within 100 miles of where I live. So... I humbly present for your consideration (and dismissal) a couple stupid Change of Plans tricks that, maybe, someone can use in a tournament to take an opponent by surprise--if only once. I&#39;d love to hear about it.<br />
<br />
Okay, first of all, Change of Plans is that stupid Fellowship rare you hated pulling. The only worse ones were all in the Sauron culture. The text?<br />
<br />
Change of Plans: &quot;Regroup: Exert a ranger to make an opponent shuffle his hand into his draw deck and draw 8 cards.&quot;<br />
<br />
Rarely, if ever, is it worth the wound to make your opponent shuffle his (or her) hand into his (or her) draw deck during the regroup phase. Admittedly, this card can mess with some of the more involved strategies, those that spend 5 sites setting up the &quot;god&quot; hand to kill you. But there are better ways to mess with such decks. Condition removal is generally one of them. Previously, the only other reason to play Change of Plans would have been pure spite; you don&#39;t want to let your opponent set up a hand, and you&#39;re gonna mess it up. Well, if you&#39;re a spiteful, non-competitive player, perhaps you were playing 4 copies of this card. So be it.<br />
<br />
Now, though, there are a couple cards from Ents of Fangorn that might actually make Change of Plans less sucky. (Yes, I realize Ents of Fangorn has been out for a while. You saw, earlier, where I wrote I haven&#39;t been able to play in a tournament for ages, right? Good. Go back and read it again and absorb all the possible implications. Fine. Let&#39;s move on...) The two cards in question increase your move limit but do so at the cost of putting all sorts of good cards into your opponent&#39;s hand. They are: Safe Paths (of the Gollum culture) and News from the Mark (of the Rohan culture).<br />
<br />
Both Safe Paths and News from the Mark are good late-game surprises, allowing you to lull your opponent into complacency, single-moving listlessly along the site path, until you triple-jump from 6 to 9 for the (possible) win. (Yes, among other things, this requires that your opponent be a poor enough player to let you triple-jump and survive. That is why this is title &quot;Stupid&quot; Change of Plans Tricks.) Unfortunately, Safe Paths allows your opponent to take ANY 3 cards from his or her discard pile into his or her hand. The text actually says &quot;up to 3,&quot; but the reality of the situation is that you&#39;re giving your opponent the best 3 cards possible to stop you. Likewise, News from the Mark allows your opponent to draw up to 6 cards (good gosh!), setting him or her up with 14 cards (!!!) as you move along. Well, that&#39;s just silly. Neither card is particularly brilliant, and you&#39;d almost be just as safe flaunting 4 cultures to play Durin&#39;s Secret and risk Grima, Chief Counselor--except that Change of Plans can almost make Safe Paths or News from the Mark worthwhile.<br />
<br />
The combination goes like this:<br />
<br />
News from the Mark --> Move limit plus one. Your opponent now has a frighteningly large and fellowship-unfriendly hand. Exert Aragorn (who else?) to play Change of Plans. Your opponent now has 8 random cards. Eh...<br />
<br />
Safe Paths --> Move limit plus one. Your opponent digs through the discard pile and takes whatever 3 cards are most likely to mess you up, and combines those with the 8 already in his or her hand. Ugly fellowship-unfriendly stuff. Exert random ranger (typically Aragorn. Let&#39;s be honest.) to play Change of Plans. Look, ma! 8 random cards. Sure, those 3 could be back in the hand, but they just might not return. Meanwhile, however, you added 5 twilight into the pool, so unless you&#39;re crazy, you probably want to play An Able Guide as well to reduce the pool by 4. (Combination = Safe Paths + Change of Plans + Able Guide.)<br />
<br />
Additionally, since you have to have at least one ranger, you might want to consider Gondor&#39;s Vengeance to discard minions during the regroup phase. It&#39;s another exertion, but it is guaranteed to get rid of a minion (think: Cave Troll, Balrog, Witch-king, etc.).<br />
<br />
Safe Paths works well with Wingchow and Hobbits. News from the Mark works best with Ranger of the North since no other ranger is likely to be as helpful to the Rohirrim (unless you consider using Arwen and Greenleaf and elf allies, including the dude that exerts to wound minions during the regroup phase).<br />
<br />
All in all, it&#39;s pretty half-arsed, but it could prove amusing. If you try it and meet with any success (at all), I&#39;d love to hear about it (like a d-mail).<br />
<br />
Cheers,<br />
Joshua &quot;Stormcrow&quot; Grace <br></font><BR><font class="bfont"> <A HREF='/lotr/articles/articles.php?id=4961&view=1&PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'>Read the Reviews</a><font class="bfont"> | <A HREF='/lotr/articles/articles.php?PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'>Back to List</A></font><p><font class="bfont"> <b>You must be a member to contribute to Decktech.</b>  <p>Please <a href='/lotr/main/join.php?PHPSESSID=...328fedb22570524062aeb1303'> become a registered member</a></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
